         <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.9471" xml:lang="en">
            <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
            <dateline>N° 3447. 6.12.01.</dateline>
            <opener>Dear Sir,</opener>
            <p>In answer to your letter I beg to say that the spindle with the whorl<note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">Dt. „der Wirbel“.</note> below is not in the Museum. In N° 6477 the spiral cut is fort he wool, and all the B. M. spindles have this spiral cut.</p>
            <p>In N° 6480 the whorl is at the top oft he stick. It has on it still a great deal of „<foreign xml:lang="fr">fil de lin</foreign>“.<note n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">Leinenfaden (leinerner Faden).</note> N° 12541 has still a small piece. We also have a spindle which does not seem to have had a whorl upon it.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>I am,<lb/> Dear Sir,<lb/> yours faithfully<lb/>
               </salute>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">EA Wallis Budge</persName>
                  <lb/>
               </signed>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">
Dr.H.Schuchardt.</persName>
               </signed>
            </closer>
            <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
         </div>
